    """
    Given a permutation p of {1, 2, ..., N},
    determine if it is possible to sort it in ascending order by swapping elements
    at most once.

    Parameters:
    stdin (str): input string in the format "N\np_1 p_2 ... p_N"

    Returns:
    str: "YES" if it is possible to sort p, "NO" otherwise
    """
    lines = stdin.split("\n")
    N = int(lines[0])
    p = [int(x) for x in lines[1].split()]

    # Check if p is a permutation of {1, 2, ..., N}
    if set(p) != set(range(1, N + 1)):
        return "NO"

    # Check if p is already sorted
    if p == list(range(1, N + 1)):
        return "YES"

    # Check if p can be sorted by swapping elements
    for i in range(N):
        if p[i] != i + 1:
            break
    else:  # If the loop completes without breaking
        return "NO"

    # Check if p can be sorted by swapping elements at index i and p[i]
    if p[i] == i + 1:
        return "NO"

    # Swap p[i] and p[p[i] - 1]
    p[i], p[p[i] - 1] = p[p[i] - 1], p[i]

    # Check if p is now sorted
    if p == list(range(1, N + 1)):
        return "YES"

    # Swap p[i] and p[p[i] - 1] again
    p[i], p[p[i] - 1] = p[p[i] - 1], p[i]

    return "NO"
